# `a` includes `b` as a submodel. Combined with `b.on` (which submodels
# `a` back), this forms a compilation-unit cycle. Building `a`'s unit
# graph recurses into `b`, which tries to recurse back into `a` — the
# back-edge sits on `b`'s `submodel a as a` declaration. The
# `CompilationCycleError` is attributed to the cycle *target* `a.on`
# (the file the cycle closes back onto, the "root of the problem"
# from this build's perspective) at `a`'s own outgoing reference
# (this `submodel b as b` line). It surfaces with the full chain:
#
#   compilation cycle detected: a.on -> b.on -> a.on
submodel b as b

X: x = 1
